The Queso Dip is phenomenal here, and it's 50% off during their M-F 4pm-6pm happy hour. I always have them add their delicious chorizo. Awesome!

The Spinach Salad is quite good...just different enough from other local salad offerings. Tender spinach with red onion, feta, bacon, and candied walnuts with a nice dressing drizzled on top. The lunch-size portion is  quite a good starter, and it's only $5.50.

The Sausage and Meatball combination on Street's happy hour menu (2:30pm - 6:00pm Mon - Fri) is a great deal...$5! Fresh, tender meatballs and Italian sausage with fennel baked in marinara and topped with gooey mozzarella cheese. Perfect with garlic bread!
The Blue Cheese and Bacon Potato Salad in the deli section is awesome. Tangy, smoky, not too creamy.
Fried zucchini with ranch...you can't beat this as a side, no matter what you pair it with...turkey, chicken, fish, or burger.
Red Robin no longer has the special happy hour pricing on appetizers...instead they have increased the appetizer prices by about a dollar, and cut the size down significantly. What a shame.

The Taquitos appetizer can't be beat...miniature spicy pork taquitos with a side of tango queso dip. So good with home-brews or margaritas. Follow with the White Sands Chimichanga...green chili burro, deep fried, and then covered with their incredible queso dip. Words can't adequately describe the goodness!
Really needed a mini-Chimi fix, with that heavenly jalapeño cream cheese. Both beef and chicken please!

BE AWARE ~~  Arizona Notary Public 's are appointed state officials and are not lawyers they can not complete documents for you.  They can only charge $2 per signature and can not legally charge you a fee to come to you.   Be wary of any Notary public telling you any thing else.   This info can be found on the Arizona secretary  of states Web page.

When cleaning your tile during the regular maintenance or moping that every home needs, remember that less is more when it comes to moisture and and cleaner.   You see, the more water you use the more the dirty water you push around settles into low spots like grout lines and residue from too much cleaner will work against you by making your floor slightly sticky.  Either one ensures you will need a professional cleaner sooner!

Vinegar = destroyed floors.....

Please don't clean your floors with vinegar and  water.  Vinegar is an acid, it eats into your grout and over time you will have chunks of grout falling out all over the floor and you won't be able to figure it out.  

If you insist on using a regular household product, go with a light mixture of ammonia and water, it is not acidic and it will leave a streak and residue free clean.  

By the way windex is made of water, ammonia, and colored dye......

Easily clean calcium off your granite counters!

That hard white buildup you get around your expensive fixtures really annoys you!  You've tried cleaners and nothing works...
